  "text": "Therefore, the function F (x (ε)) is concave. Hence, we can apply the pipage rounding directly: We start with the fractional solution x * (obtained using the algorithm from Theorem 1.4). At every step, we pick e and e (using the algorithm from Calinescu et al. [CITATION_1] ) and move tox (ε) with ε = ε 1 = − min{x e , 1 − x e } or ε = ε 2 = min{1 − x e , x e }, whichever minimizes the concave function F (x (ε)) on the interval [ε 1 , ε 2 ]. We stop when the current solutionx is integral.",
